            "notes": "Ubuntu does not have a system supplied package for librealsense, but it can be installed from the vendor (Intel) by adding the following repo to your system:<div class=\"code-box-copy\">\n<button class=\"code-box-copy__btn\" data-clipboard-target=\"#realU22\" title=\"Copy\"></button><pre class=\"language-shell\" id=\"realU22\">sudo apt-get -y install curl apt-transport-https lsb-core\nsudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/keyrings\nsudo curl -sSf https://librealsense.intel.com/Debian/librealsense.pgp | tee /etc/apt/keyrings/librealsense.pgp > /dev/null\nsudo echo \"deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/librealsense.pgp] https://librealsense.intel.com/Debian/apt-repo `lsb_release -cs` main\" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/librealsense.list > /dev/null\nsudo apt-get update</pre></div>"
